rComments: Agree with comment posted 01/04/2016. Prof's explanations are fine when looked at one by one, but fairly disorganized when put together (makes no distinction between 2-3 different topics). Labs can be challenging even in groups, and requires you to understand course material taught basically the night before.
he doesn't care about his students, bad marker, midterms are full of mistakes. I submitted tens of assignments but he didn't mark one

He is not so bad as most people suggested here. His notes are quite hard to follow on the blackboard but his online videos can help. If you try to ask him questions he may not be so willing to answer after the lecture though.

Labs/pre-labs are always ahead of lecture material, no one in a lab session got above 5 (out of 10)! lab report is ok but he wants u to draw 5-10 Oscilloscope pic by hand (even worse, report is due @ the end of lab), why not just let a TA check and sign? Homework is fair, wouldnt recommend taking it if you are looking for a kernel breadth course.

I liked his style of teaching. His lectures were quite well planned with much thought on how to make it understandable.  It's hard to reach him through email, but if you talk to him in person, he is very helpful.
he rarely goes to school. not helpful and don't wait for a reply to your emails. difficult assignments, average is C

rComments: Great guy who cares about his students. His lectures are clear and he takes the time to explain any questions people may have. The mandatory problems sets also helps everyone keep up to date on the material. He aims for a high-ish average although if it gets too high he'll bring it down with a really hard exam.
Excellent instructor - I don't really get the previous ratings, I thought he was fantastic.
He has no idea about power systems.

Midterm average was 20%...he is doing something wrong when its that low. Lectures are boring and I didn't feel like I learned much. We had final presentations and he was sick so he was in a grumpy mood and slept thru most presentations, very unprofessional! Anyways, he is nice during office hours and helpful... but yea wont take with him again.
Zeb Tate is an amazing professor. He explains everything well and has good knowledge on the subject. He also records every lecture which is helpful and is really cute. Hope to have him again.
Tough exams and midterms, but teaches the material very well. Also a very funny guy.
Tough courses, concepts clearly explained. Everyone gets A anyways because bell curve. Nicest guy, very knowledgeable and passionate about energy systems.
